This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney, who is on Air Force One en route to Colorado Springs. Carney mentions that President Obama will be delivering the commencement address at the Air Force Academy and will likely talk about the changes that have occurred over the past four years, as well as the need to support veterans when they return home. Carney also discusses the ongoing nuclear talks with Iran and the importance of reciprocal actions. He mentions that the talks are taking place in Baghdad and that the administration hopes for progress. Carney also addresses the issue of federal spending under the Obama administration, stating that federal spending has actually increased at a slower pace than under previous presidents. He defends the administration's approach to fiscal responsibility and deficit reduction. Carney concludes by mentioning the President's upcoming fundraisers and a speech by Mitt Romney on education, and he expresses the President's support for education reform.